            <div type=”letter”>
                <opener><dateline><date when="1918-02-05">February 5 1918</dateline></date>
                    <salute>Dear <persName key="harriet_monroe">Harriet:–</persName></salute></opener>
                <p>I am very glad that you like <title key="appuldercombePark" level="a">&quot;appuldercombe Park.&quot;</title> Of course it is 
                    in the vein of <title key="patterns" level="a">&quot;Patterns,&quot;</title> but it is so different. One is a bad woman, and one is a good woman. 
                    In one, the woman goes insane, in the other she differences, these slight changes that put a different phase on everything, which is to me interesting. 
                    I am sorry you do not like <title key="misericordia" level="a">“Misericordia”</title> well enough to take. I never intended it to go 
                    with &quot;Appuldercombe Park.&quot; I thought it might come out another time; but, of course, just as you say.  </p>
                <p></p>
                <closer> Affectionately yours,</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
